              margin-top: 2px !important;">US probes DeepSeek over Nvidia chip access via Singapore</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-31-1.png" alt="US probes DeepSeek over Nvidia chip access via Singapore" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">US officials are probing whether DeepSeek gained access to <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-31-01-2025-h1-1-nvidia-latest-chip?source=website" target="_blank">Nvidia’s latest chips</a> via Singapore. Nvidia’s latest chips used for artificial intelligence tasks are banned from being sold to China as per US export restrictions. However, given DeepSeek’s remarkable rise and the R1 model’s performance, many believe the startup gained access to the latest chip via any Asian country. Nvidia earns 20% of its revenue from Singapore. The company maintains that its partners comply with export laws but faces scrutiny over potential diversions. Many shipments associated with Singapore were shipped to other locations, raising concerns about potential diversions.</p>
        </mj-text>
